Name: Function
Description: The name of the function being called.

Name: ProprietaryOperator
Description: When the source language used an infix or prefix operator to invoke the function, this is the symbol that represents that operator.

Name: IsProprietary
Description: When true, the Function property contains the name of a system-specfied function. When false, the Function property contains the name of a harmonized function as documented at TODO.

Name: Arguments
Description: A list of parameters to the function.
